title: Windows Defender Found Trojan:Win32/Vigorf.A and Trojan:Win32/AgentTesla!ml - Virus, Trojan, Spyware, and Malware Removal Help
text:
Windows Defender shows the viruses in its results but when I click "Remove" or "Quarantine", nothing happens. Unsure why. I noticed the past three nights that when I try and shut down the computer, it takes ages. One time I left the computer on while I went outside, and when I returned four hours later the PC still hadn't shut down (it showed "Shutting down" with the rotational circle and that was it). I had to force a shutdown, and when I started it up this time a blue screen appeared and I picked the "Restart" option. Viruses would explain the issues but I'm unsure how they got past the firewall. FRST and Addition below. Please delete the other (duplicate) posts with similar content I posted (I posted them because I thought this one hadn't posted correctly, I got sent to a "Cloudflare" error page when I tried posting each one, and then when I posted a third time they all showed as posted to the forum after all).
